e larger context of identity formation and emerging nationalism which marked United States history in the nineteenth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aBannock IndiansxEthnic identity. 0aBannock IndiansxReligion. 0aBannock IndiansxRites and ceremonies. 0aGhost dancexHistoryx19th century. 0aGhost dancexHistoryy19th century. 0aShoshoni IndiansxEthnic identity. 0aShoshoni IndiansxReligion. 0aShoshoni IndiansxRites and ceremonies. 7aRELIGION / Ethnic & Tribal.2bisacsh  a19th century american history.  a19th century native american history.  aamerican indian ghost dance movement.  aamerican indians.  abannocks.  acultural studies.  aethnogenesis.  aghost dance.  ahistory.  aidentity.  aindigenous cultures.  aindigenous peoples.  amissionary.  anationalism.  anative american culture.  anative americans.  anative peoples.  anew religion.  apolitics.  aprophets.  arace in america.  areligion.  areservation life.  ashamans.  ashoshones.  asocial identity.  aspiritual.  asupernatural forces.  aunited states government.  aunited states of america.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094172440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520941724423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520941724/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles